properties.name: 9:30 Club
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 815 V. St This is where i have my absolute happiest memory. My two best friends at the time, Jacque and Kelly, and I all loved this band stephen kellogg and the sixers, so for my 16th birthday they bought us tickets to go see them at the 9:30 Club. It was so much fun.

properties.name: ALexandria Farmers Market
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 301 King Street Alexandria, VAThis is where i have my first memory. Sometimes really early satruday mornings my mom and I would meet her sister at this farmers market. I\'m not sure how old I was but i remember smelling boxwoods and cinnamon and that my mom was looking down on me wearing a very bright pink turtle neck.

properties.name: Alexandria Hospital
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 4320 Seminary Ed Alexandria, VAThis is the Hospital i was born in.

properties.name: Buckingham Fountain
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 Grant Park , Chicago , IL When i came to visit Columbia i remember walking up to Grant Park and seeing this fountain. I\'m not even sure why or what exactly happened but i just felt so happy there that i knew this is where i wanted to go to college.

properties.name: Jammin Java
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 227 Maple Ave E, Vienna, VAThis is the spot where i went to see tons and tons of shows with all of my friends, and it is also where i got my first kiss a very long time ago.

properties.name: Kilmer Middle School
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 8100 wolftrap rdThis is where i went to middle school and also where i met 8 guys that i became really good friends with. It was 8th grade and they sat at my lunch table, for some reason they nicknamed me Sweater, and we became really good friends. This time period of the middle to the end of 8th grade was one of the happiest of my life.

properties.name: Lake Anna
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 6800 Lawyers Rd, Fredericksburg, VAThis is where we took Jim to be buried. His family had owned a plot here for a very long time. This is also where a few years before Jim died we came down for Thanksgiving dinner with Jim and his family because they had a Lake House.

properties.name: Loudoun County High School
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 Dry mill rd leesburg, vaThis is the high school i transferred to at the beginning of my junior year. I met a lot of cool people here but overall most of the time i just really didn\'t like this school. It was way stricter and just not as fun as Marshall.

properties.name: Loudoun Hospital
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 44045 riverside parkwayThis is where the owner of my barn Jim died. He had had cancer for a few years but always seemed to find a way to bounce back until one day my mom picked me up from school and sped all the way to the hospital so i could say goodbye. Luckily i was able to and Jim died the next morning. He was incredibly important to me.

properties.name: Marshall High School
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 7731 leesburg pikeFor freshman and sophomore year this was my high school. This is also where i met my best friend to this day Jacquelyn Bill. She moved here in the middle of freshman year and we became really fast friends. She moved back to where she was originally from at the end of sophomore year, and that had a really big impact on my life.

properties.name: My First House
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 1609 Fremont Lane vienna, va 22182This is where i lived for the first 16 years of my life.

properties.name: New Years Eve Party 1998
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 I was in 2nd grade when this event took place. My mom, my dad, and I were all at this big New Years Eve Party that everyone that was in my parents circle of friends was at. While i still don\'t know everything that happened something bad happened and because of this night that group of friends stopped hanging out with my parents. If this night had never happened then my life would be so different because a few months after it happened the entire group of friends decided to move to a neighborhood that was being built in Great Falls, VA.

properties.name: Rock Hill Farm
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 15483 Limestone school rd leesburg, va 20176This is the house i moved into when i was 16. We moved here the summer in between my freshman and sophomore years. I could have chosen to stay back in vienna but Jacque had just moved and i decided it was time for a change.

properties.name: Shadybrook Stables
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 1033 Belleview Rd mclean, va 22102This is where i rode horses. I started when i was 8 years old. I had lots of friends here for many years and was at the barn almost everyday. The owner of the barn Jim was a huge impact on my life and i considered him like a father to me.

properties.name: Tysons Corner Center
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 mcleanvaThis is the place where i figured out that the first guy i ever really really liked didn\'t like me back. I also used to spend a lot of free time here when i was in 8th and 9th grade.

properties.name: University Center
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 525 S. State St Chicago Il 60605This is where i\'m living right now, and while coming to college doesn\'t really feel like its had a huge impact on my life yet its still a big change and i\'m sure that it will have a large impact.

properties.name: Westbriar Elementary School
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 1741 Pine Valley Dr vienna, vaThis is where i went to elementary school. On the first day of kindergarten i cried because i didn\'t want to leave my mom, but by the end of the year i cried because i didn\'t want to stop going to school for the summer.

properties.name: Worcester Polytechnic Institute
properties.description: Posted by Emilyquin10 100 Institute Rd Worcester, MA 01609This is the college that my brother went to. He left for college when i was 3 years old and i remember being very sad about it, and i feel like i\'ve never really gotten as close with him because he never really lived at home while i\'ve been alive.
